	<title>IE7: Mousemove event binding broken on Boxes</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Firefox3_ Safari4 work fine.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">IE7 throws the following error as it attempts to bind the mousemove event:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">All of the logging I ve done has shown that the the mousemove event is never fired which leads me to believe the binding is not working in the first place.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">However a work around has been found.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">1 Click and hold the titlebar of the box as if to drag it</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">2 Drop the box back in the same place which it rested previously before dragging was initiated</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">3 Click on the widget to activate the javascript</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.4">4 notice that the ratings stars will now follow your mouse allowing you to vote.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">You can add a demo app here:
http://apps.facebook.com/csitop_clips/</sentence>
		</paragraph>
